{
  "page": "Monford Velaryon",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/50px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/75px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/100px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Monford Velaryon</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/50px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/75px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/100px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Monford_and_Monterys_Velaryon_by_anguine-acuity.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Monford and Monterys Velaryon by anguine-acuity.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b9/Monford_and_Monterys_Velaryon_by_anguine-acuity.jpg/300px-Monford_and_Monterys_Velaryon_by_anguine-acuity.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"313\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b9/Monford_and_Monterys_Velaryon_by_anguine-acuity.jpg/450px-Monford_and_Monterys_Velaryon_by_anguine-acuity.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b9/Monford_and_Monterys_Velaryon_by_anguine-acuity.jpg/600px-Monford_and_Monterys_Velaryon_by_anguine-acuity.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Lord Monford Velaryon and his son Monterys by anguine-acuity</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_Driftmark\" title=\"Master of Driftmark\">Master of Driftmark</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Race</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyrian</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nIn or before <a href=\"/index.php/281_AC\" title=\"281 AC\">281&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafmonford_velaryon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafmonford_velaryon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/299_AC\" title=\"299 AC\">299&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Blackwater Rush</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Monterys_Velaryon\" title=\"Monterys Velaryon\">Monterys Velaryon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Monford Velaryon</b> is the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_Driftmark\" title=\"Master of Driftmark\">Master of Driftmark</a>, and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Aurane_Waters\" title=\"Aurane Waters\">Aurane Waters</a>, the Bastard of <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a>, is his <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> half-brother.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafmonford_velaryon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafmonford_velaryon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Monford_Velaryon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Monford is handsome with long, fair hair. He sometimes wears sea-green <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a> with a white <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> seahorse brooch.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Monford favors aggressive maneuvers in warfare.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racokprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racokprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Lowborn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lowborn\">lowborn</a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> believes that the <a href=\"/index.php/Highborn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Highborn\">highborn</a> Lord Velaryon would never confide in him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Monford_Velaryon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Monford_Velaryon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>As a vassal of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>, Monford supports <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>'s claim to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>. However, he threatens to take his forces home if they do not strike soon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Lord Monford is present when <a href=\"/index.php/Melisandre\" title=\"Melisandre\">Melisandre</a> burns statues of <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">the Seven</a> taken from the <a href=\"/index.php/Sept_at_Dragonstone\" title=\"Sept at Dragonstone\">sept at Dragonstone</a>; Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> notices that Monford watches Stannis rather than the conflagration.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Monford wants Stannis to sail from Dragonstone to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to challenge King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a>, but Stannis instead sails to <a href=\"/index.php/Shipbreaker_Bay\" title=\"Shipbreaker Bay\">Shipbreaker Bay</a> against his brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a>. During the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">siege of Storm's End</a>, Stannis thinks that Lord Velaryon wants to assault the castle instead of starving it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, Lord Velaryon's <i><a href=\"/index.php/Pride_of_Driftmark\" title=\"Pride of Driftmark\">Pride of Driftmark</a></i> crashes between two Lannister river runners, but is later set ablaze with <a href=\"/index.php/Wildfire\" title=\"Wildfire\">wildfire</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Aurane_Waters\" title=\"Aurane Waters\">Aurane Waters</a>, Monford's half brother, kneels to Joffrey after the battle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Monford_Velaryon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>It is reported by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alester_Florent\" title=\"Alester Florent\">Alester Florent</a> that Lord Monford burned with <i>Pride of Driftmark</i> on the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Rush\" title=\"Blackwater Rush\">Blackwater Rush</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He is succeeded by his young son, <a href=\"/index.php/Monterys_Velaryon\" title=\"Monterys Velaryon\">Monterys Velaryon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Monford_Velaryon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Davos would have given much to know what he was thinking, but one such as Velaryon would never confide in him. The <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a> was of the blood of ancient <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">his House</a> had thrice provided brides for <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> princes; Davos Seaworth stank of fish and onions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The others bobbed their heads up and down like a flock of geese, all but Velaryon, who said that <a href=\"/index.php/Steel\" title=\"Steel\">steel</a> would decide <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">the matter</a>, not words on parchment. As if I had never suspected.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Lord Velaryon will urge me to <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">storm the castle walls</a> at first light, grapnels and scaling ladders against arrows and boiling oil. The young mules will think this a splendid notion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;